    {
      "text": "Which of the following benefits is not offered under the ESI Act?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Unemployment Allowance",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Paid Vacation Time",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Funeral Expenses",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Rehabilitation Allowance",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. Paid Vacation Time",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:779px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Benefits of ESI(Employees State Insurance) Act.</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Medical Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Provides \"full medical care,\" including <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"277d6f3ee2169277718938e321258f\">hospitalization</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1a8e8831bb1692777182ce2c8a751f\">at no</span> cost to insured individuals & families in cases of sickness, employment injury, and maternity.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Sickness Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Provides <strong>70% </strong>of average daily wages in cash during medical leave for a maximum of 91 days within 365 days, as certified by the Insurance Medical Officer/Practitioner.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Extended <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"73c1caf8d11692777198b1248373d3\">Sickness</span> Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Extended coverage for long-term diseases beyond 91 days; 34 diseases covered if employed for two years.</p>\n<p>Extended <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"73c1caf8d11692777198b1248373d3\">sickness</span> benefit is paid at <strong>80% </strong>of the insured person's wages.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Enhanced <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"73c1caf8d11692777198b1248373d3\">Sickness</span> Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><u>Cash benefits (100% wages) for sterilisation procedures:</u>\n<ul>\n<li>14 days for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2a6989bad01692777201a73b82b799\">tubectomy</span> (women),</li>\n<li>7 days for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8b8c53004d1692777201cf3df335f5\">vasectomy</span> (men).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Maternity Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><u>Cash payments for childbirth, miscarriage, or pregnancy-related sickness:</u>\n<ul>\n<li>26 weeks for childbirth,</li>\n<li>6 weeks for miscarriage, and</li>\n<li>40 days for pregnancy-related sickness.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Paid at 100% of the insured woman's average daily wages.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Disablement Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><u>Temporary Disablement Benefit (TDB): </u>\n<ul>\n<li>90% of wages paid from day one for temporary employment injury, until recovery.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><u>Permanent Disablement Benefit (PDB): </u>\n<ul>\n<li>90% of wages paid monthly for life, based on certified loss of earning capacity.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Dependent's Benefit</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Dependents receive 90% of the deceased's (due to employment injuries) wages as a shared pension, eligible until age 18 or earlier for married daughters.</li>\n<li><strong>If daughter marries before 18 the benefit is withdrawn</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Funeral Expenses</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option C)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Offers a cash payment up to <strong>Rs. 15,000</strong> to cover funeral expenses upon the death of an insured individual.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Rehabilitation</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option D)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Insured individuals and their families are entitled to continued medical treatment even after permanent disablement or retirement.</li>\n<li>They have to pay a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"01cc201eb616927771937a9ae6c669\">nominal</span> fee of Rs.10 per month to avail this benefit.</li>\n<li>Rehabilitation <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f8330e788f16927771812e4f73b80c\">allowance</span> of Rs.15,000 granted.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Unemployment allowance</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option A)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>For eligible employees due to factory <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2b4569285f1692777184282b1ca3f1\">closure</span> or retrenchment: 50% of wage for up to two years.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
